.TH "drm_dp_dsc_sink_supported_input_bpcs" 9 "drm_dp_dsc_sink_supported_input_bpcs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_dsc_sink_supported_input_bpcs \- Get all the input bits per component values supported by the DSC sink.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dp_dsc_sink_supported_input_bpcs
.BI "(const u8 dsc_dpcd[DP_DSC_RECEIVER_CAP_SIZE] "  ","
.BI "u8 dsc_bpc[3] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dsc_dpcd" 12
DSC capabilities from DPCD
.IP "dsc_bpc" 12
An array to be filled by this helper with supported
input bpcs.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read the DSC DPCD from the sink device to parse the supported bits per
component values. This is used to populate the DSC parameters
in the \fIstruct drm_dsc_config\fP by the driver.
Driver creates an infoframe using these parameters to populate
\fIstruct drm_dsc_pps_infoframe\fP. These are sent to the sink using DSC
infoframe using the helper function \fBdrm_dsc_pps_infoframe_pack\fP
.SH "RETURN"
Number of input BPC values parsed from the DPCD
